208–1260":"1208–1260","1230–1283":"1230–1283","1235–1291":"1235–1291","1205–Male":"1205–Deceased","1205":"1205","abt 1205":"about 1205","1235":"1235","1230":"1230","Abt 1235":"about 1235","1283":"1283","1260":"1260","1291":"1291","1208":"1208","Ireland":"Ireland","ireland":"Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Neill","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Kieran, Seamus, Siobhan, Dermot, Liam, Nuala, Bridie, Brigid, Conor, Fintan, John Patrick.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Néill</b> ‘descendant of <i>Niall</i>’, an Irish personal name possibly derived from <i>néal</i> ‘cloud’ (see   Neil  ).","History: Bearers of this surname mostly claim descent from Niall Noígíallach (Niall of the Nine Hostages), a legendary king of Ireland who flourished in the 5th century. His descendants, the Ui Neill dynasty, dominated Ireland, on and off, from the 6th to the 10th century. The surname itself can be traced with some confidence to one of these descendants, namely Niall Glúndubh mac Aodha (died 919), High King of Ireland from 911 to 919, with a power base in Tyrone, Ulster."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Neall","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"McNelis","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Dermot, Brendan.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Niallghuis</b> ‘son of <i>Niallghus</i>’, a personal name (intended as complimentary) composed of the personal name <i>Niall</i> (see   O'Neill  ) + <i>gus</i> ‘vigor’. In Irish the combination of [k] and [n] was generally pronounced [kr], Anglicized as the variants   McCreless   and   McCrillis  ."]},{"name":"O'Neal","meanings":["Irish (Longford, Down): variant of   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"O'Niel","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"Odneal","meanings":["Perhaps an irregular variant of Irish   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"Nealon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Declan.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Nialláin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Niallán</i>’, a personal name formed from a diminutive of <i>Niall</i>, see   O'Neill  ,   Neil  ."]},{"name":"O'Neil","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Conn, Donal, Liam, Siobhan, Aileen, Eamon, Michael Patrick, Seamus, Sean Patrick, William Sean.","Irish (Mayo, Tipperary): variant of   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"Neil","meanings":["Scottish, English (Lancashire), and Irish (Munster): from the Gaelic personal name <i>Niall</i> (genitive <i>Néill</i>), possibly derived from Irish <i>néal</i> ‘cloud’. In most cases the name probably represents a shortened form of the derived patronymics   McNeill   or the comparable Irish   O'Neill  .","English: variant of   Neal  ."]},{"name":"O'Neel","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Neill  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"O'Neill was born about 1205, in Ireland. He had at least 2 sons with Cecily MacLochlain."},"et":{"abt 1205–":"umbes 1205–Surnud","1208–1260":"1208–1260","1230–1283":"1230–1283","1235–1291":"1235–1291","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1205":"1205","abt 1205":"umbes 1205","1235":"1235","1230":"1230","Abt 1235":"umbes 1235","1283":"1283","1260":"1260","1291":"1291","1208":"1208","Ireland":"Iirimaa","ireland":"Iirimaa"},"fi":{"abt 1205–":"noin 1205–Kuollut","1208–1260":"1208–1260","1230–1283":"1230–1283","1235–1291":"1235–1291","1205–Male":"1205–Kuollut","1205":"1205","abt 1205":"noin 1205","1235":"1235","1230":"1230","Abt 1235":"noin 1235","1283":"1283","1260":"1260","1291":"1291","1208":"1208","Ireland":"Irlanti","ireland":"Irlanti"},"fr":{"abt 1205–":"environ 1205–Décédé","1208–1260":"1208–1260","1230–1283":"1230–1283","1235–1291":"1235–1291","1205–Male":"1205–Décédé","1205":"1205","abt 1205":"environ 1205","1235":"1235","1230":"1230","Abt 1235":"environ 1235","1283":"1283","1260":"1260","1291":"1291","1208":"1208","Ireland":"Irlande","ireland":"Irlande","lifeSummary":"O'Neill est né environ 1205, à Irlande. Il a eu au mo